## BUSINESS MODEL — HOW CLIENTS PAY

### Three Tiers

**Tier 1 — Listing**
Small fee. Client gets featured inside an existing roundup or directory post that Mirellé already created and ranked.

**Tier 2 — Dedicated Post**
Medium fee. Client gets their own standalone post on the platform. Written editorially. Ranks for their name, service, and location.

**Tier 3 — Campaign**
Larger fee. Multiple posts over weeks or months. Client selects which post types they want and how long the campaign runs. Preset packages available so clients do not have to build their own.

### What Each Client Type Buys

Salons and nail techs buy local visibility — they want their name and services ranking in their city and area.

Brands buy national awareness — product launches, trend features, editorial coverage that ranks across the whole country.

Influencers buy credibility and discoverability — press features, portfolio pages, and collab listings that rank for their name and get them brand deals.

