## POST STRUCTURE — CLIENT ACQUISITION (Type A)

Every post follows this exact 8-component structure. No reordering. No skipping.

| # | Component | What It Does |
|---|-----------|--------------|
| 1 | SEO Title | Exact search phrase the business owner types into Google |
| 2 | Hook | One line hitting their pain point immediately — no warmup |
| 3 | Pain Block | 2-3 paragraphs in their language — makes them feel understood |
| 4 | Solution Bridge | Introduces Mirellé editorially as the answer — never salesy |
| 5 | What You Offer | 3-4 bullets — what they get, not how the platform works |
| 6 | Stats / Credibility | 3 real market stats with context — builds trust before the ask |
| 7 | FAQ | 3-5 real objections from suspicious business owners answered honestly |
| 8 | CTA | Mailto button → contact@mirelleinspo.com |

**Primary keyword rule:** Appears naturally twice in the pain block. After that, semantic data carries topical authority. No mechanical keyword density tracking.

**Tone:** Editorial, authoritative, direct. Sharp industry insider who understands the nail business world. Never salesy. Never generic. British English only.

